.TH GIT-PRS 1 "2026-07-08" "git-tools" "Git Tools Manual"
.SH NAME
git-prs \- print the URL of every open PR you have authored in this repo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git prs
[\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-title\fR]
.br
.B git prs
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print one URL per line \(em nothing else \(em for every open pull request whose
author is you in the current repository. The plain, one-link-per-line output is
easy to skim or pipe into another command. With
.BR \-\-title ,
each line becomes
.IR "<link> -- <title>" .
.PP
The repository is taken from the current directory's remote, and your login from
the authenticated
.B gh
session, so there is nothing to configure.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-title
Append each PR's title, printing
.I <link> -- <title>
instead of just the link.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage and exit.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Requires the GitHub CLI
.RB ( gh ),
authenticated
.RB ( "gh auth login" ).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B git prs
Print a link for each of your open PRs.
.TP
.B git prs | pbcopy
Copy the list of links to the clipboard.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr (1),
.BR git-done (1),
.BR gh (1)
